    line-height: 1.6;"><p>Derek sat in his small, dingy apartment, feeling the weight of his loneliness pressing down on him. He had always been a recluse, preferring the company of his thoughts over the bustle of the outside world. But lately, his isolation had started to gnaw at him, leaving him feeling empty and disconnected.</p>
